Yehi'am (Hebrew: יְחִיעָם‎) is a kibbutz in northern Israel. Located the western Upper Galilee, eight miles east of the coastal town of Nahariya and 14 miles south-east of the border with Lebanon it falls under the jurisdiction of Mateh Asher Regional Council. In 2016 it had a population of 642. It is located around 365 meters above sea level
Yehiam is situated next to the ruins of the Ottoman-era castle of Jiddin, built on top of the 13th-century Crusader castle of Judin.
